title: Independent Candidate Muhammad Sohail Afridi Shah wins PK-70 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Muhammad Sohail Afridi has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-70, Khyber-II by securing 31,649 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League-N (PML-N) candidate Bilal Afridi who bagged 7,401 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 26.22 per cent.
